and you didn't tell me?

287
00:11:03,759 --> 00:11:04,559
Does that make any sense?

288
00:11:04,679 --> 00:11:05,559
And Yitong, you're suspicious too.

289
00:11:05,679 --> 00:11:06,759
You two must be
hiding something from me.

290
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:10,679
Right here.

291
00:11:11,639 --> 00:11:12,320
Xiao.

292
00:11:14,919 --> 00:11:16,360
We found the info
on the incoming call number.

293
00:11:16,919 --> 00:11:18,240
The original owner's ID was lost once.

294
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,440
Afterwards, this ID was used

295
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:20,399
to get seven phone cards.

296
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:22,320
Seven phone cards?

297
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:22,840
Yes.

298
00:11:23,799 --> 00:11:24,559
Think hard.

299
00:11:24,639 --> 00:11:25,879
Have you two offended anyone recently?

300
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:26,879
Or had any financial disputes

301
00:11:26,879 --> 00:11:27,879
with anyone?

302
00:11:28,039 --> 00:11:29,120
Or do you yourselves

303
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:30,120
have any suspects in mind?

304
00:11:30,279 --> 00:11:31,039
Anything at all.

305
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:32,440
Think hard, try to remember.

306
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:33,039
Jiang Juan.

307
00:11:37,559 --> 00:11:38,200
Jiang Juan?

308
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:42,120
After Wenwen and her grandma
were kidnapped,

309
00:11:42,519 --> 00:11:43,759
she vanished as well.

310
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:55,919
Time to eat, come on.

311
00:12:04,919 --> 00:12:05,399
Eat.

312
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:08,600
I'll go feed her.

313
00:12:12,639 --> 00:12:13,200
Come on.

314
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:14,759
Ma'am.

315
00:12:17,679 --> 00:12:18,440
Smells pretty good, huh?

316
00:12:19,559 --> 00:12:20,519
Here, let me feed you.

317
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:22,200
Come on.

318
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:24,159
Eat up.

319
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:26,720
What are you whimpering for?
You want to starve?

320
00:12:26,879 --> 00:12:27,480
Forget about it.

321
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,000
Come on, eat.

322
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,000
My grandma is sick.

323
00:12:29,519 --> 00:12:30,480
Then she certainly needs to eat.

324
00:12:30,879 --> 00:12:31,360
Come on now.

325
00:12:31,879 --> 00:12:32,360
Open up.

326
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:33,600
Hurry.

327
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:34,720
Don't test me.

328
00:12:34,759 --> 00:12:35,399
I'm warning you.

329
00:12:35,559 --> 00:12:36,279
What's wrong with you?

330
00:12:37,279 --> 00:12:38,080
Let me check.

331
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:42,759
She's burning up.

332
00:12:43,279 --> 00:12:43,919
She has a fever.

333
00:12:44,159 --> 00:12:44,639
Go get medicine.

334
00:12:44,759 --> 00:12:46,000
A fever? It can't be that serious.

335
00:12:46,519 --> 00:12:47,159
Just go.

336
00:12:50,919 --> 00:12:51,600
She's a hostage,

337
00:12:51,639 --> 00:12:52,600
not your grandma.

338
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:54,679
Cut the crap.

339
00:13:13,399 --> 00:13:13,879
Here.

340
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:15,240
Drink some warm water.

341
00:13:18,759 --> 00:13:19,399
Careful.

342
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:27,200
Ms. Jiang,

343
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:30,039
can you face your own child?

344
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:33,879
If you get arrested,

345
00:13:34,519 --> 00:13:37,200
she'll never see you again.

346
00:13:50,879 --> 00:13:52,600
I know I'm doing the wrong thing.

347
00:13:57,759 --> 00:13:59,519
Honestly, I envy you so much.

348
00:14:00,759 --> 00:14:01,879
Every time I see Wenwen,

349
00:14:02,639 --> 00:14:03,879
it's like seeing my own little girl.

350
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:08,720
I haven't seen her for so many years.

351
00:14:10,559 --> 00:14:11,559
The last time I saw her,

352
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:12,919
she had just gotten her hair braided.

353
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:14,919
Back then,

354
00:14:14,919 --> 00:14:16,240
I braided her hair every day.

355
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:18,279
A different style each day.

356
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:28,120
I just have to get the money.

357
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:33,919
I need to bring her out here.

358
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:40,399
Her dad did beat me.

359
00:14:43,279 --> 00:14:43,799
I remember

360
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,200
the last time he beat me,

361
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:47,960
he kicked my spleen until it ruptured.

362
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,679
If I hadn't run away, I would've died.

363
00:14:55,559 --> 00:14:56,600
With my little girl living with him,

364
00:14:58,080 --> 00:14:59,919
there's no way she's had a good life.

365
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:03,000
Later on,

366
00:15:03,519 --> 00:15:04,600
I did some things.

367
00:15:06,120 --> 00:15:07,279
There's no going back now.

368
00:15:09,399 --> 00:15:10,279
For so many years,

369
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:13,919
it's been a living hell for me.

370
00:15:15,879 --> 00:15:17,240
No matter what you say, it's useless.

371
00:15:17,519 --> 00:15:18,679
You're a horrible person.

372
00:15:18,799 --> 00:15:19,519
A kidnapper.

373
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:20,919
Wenwen.

374
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,240
Ms. Jiang,

375
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:28,799
this is a gift for you.

376
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:30,480
Put it on.

377
00:15:31,039 --> 00:15:33,039
You'll look like a fairy from heaven.

378
00:15:33,519 --> 00:15:34,480
Grandma says

379
00:15:34,759 --> 00:15:36,440
kids turning twelve face bad luck.

380
00:15:36,879 --> 00:15:37,799
Didn't you say your daughter

381
00:15:37,799 --> 00:15:38,759
is about my age?

382
00:15:39,320 --> 00:15:40,559
I got her a pair of socks

383
00:15:40,639 --> 00:15:41,480
and a charm bracelet.

384
00:15:41,879 --> 00:15:42,840
These things really work.

385
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:44,440
Wenwen bought

386
00:15:44,799 --> 00:15:45,840
these two.

387
00:15:46,279 --> 00:15:47,399
She usually spends

388
00:15:47,559 --> 00:15:49,399
all her pocket money on snacks.

389
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:50,840
Guess she's growing up.

390
00:15:50,879 --> 00:15:51,679
She learned to be thoughtful.

391
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,240
My dear daughter,

392
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:02,200
I can't turn back now.

393
00:16:17,279 --> 00:16:17,840
Zinuo.

394
00:16:18,919 --> 00:16:19,519
Zinuo.

395
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:22,639
How is it?

396
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:25,080
There are some things
I must tell you face to face.

397
00:16:25,639 --> 00:16:26,720
Your mom isn't the one
who kidnapped them.

398
00:16:27,639 --> 00:16:28,960
After Ming gave her the money,

399
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:30,519
he got a call from the real kidnapper.

400
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,519
So your mom used this situation

401
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:34,120
to swindle the money away.

402
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:35,799
Now, we have no way

403
00:16:35,799 --> 00:16:36,720
to save the hostages.

404
00:16:37,159 --> 00:16:38,080
Your mom's now holding

405
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:38,960
two lives in her hands.

406
00:16:39,519 --> 00:16:40,279
So you absolutely must

407
00:16:40,279 --> 00:16:41,320
talk to your mom.

408
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:42,279
Make her give the money back.

409
00:16:42,279 --> 00:16:43,240
Even just 30 million is fine.

410
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,399
We must save those two first.

411
00:16:44,399 --> 00:16:45,399
She can take all the rest.

412
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:53,840
Once she got the money,
she won't return it.

413
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:55,080
She can't do it.

414
00:16:57,159 --> 00:16:57,679
Unless we

415
00:16:57,679 --> 00:16:58,559
have something she wants.

416
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:00,519
What thing?

417
00:17:09,759 --> 00:17:10,359
Zinuo.

418
00:17:10,559 --> 00:17:11,240
Li Jin swindled Yu Ming

419
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:12,279
out of the money they needed
to save lives.

420
00:17:12,799 --> 00:17:13,920
You were involved in this too,

421
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:14,720
weren't you?

422
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:16,279
Lei,

423
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:17,519
do you even know

424
00:17:17,519 --> 00:17:18,319
what you're doing?

425
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:19,720
Why are you helping her?

426
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:21,359
She's doing this

427
00:17:21,599 --> 00:17:22,519
for you.

428
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,880
This money that your dad left behind

429
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:26,880
is your future security.

430
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:29,279
How many times
have I said I don't need it?

431
00:17:29,519 --> 00:17:30,960
She keeps saying it's for me.

432
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,400
Has she ever considered my feelings?

433
00:17:32,839 --> 00:17:34,160
I'm just an excuse for her evil.

434
00:17:34,599 --> 00:17:35,359
Think about it carefully.

435
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:36,759
Who really needs this money?

436
00:17:37,079 --> 00:17:37,880
Is it me,

437
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:39,279
or is it her?

438
00:17:39,759 --> 00:17:40,319
Zinuo,

439
00:17:40,839 --> 00:17:41,960
you've misunderstood her.

440
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:44,640
She's changed.

441
00:17:45,079 --> 00:17:45,960
If she had truly changed,

442
00:17:47,119 --> 00:17:48,079
she wouldn't be scheming

443
00:17:48,079 --> 00:17:49,240
to steal
other people's life-saving money.

444
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:50,680
If because of this money,

445
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:52,799
Yu Wenwen and Fan Meijuan

446
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:54,359
end up like Chen Liyang,

447
00:17:54,839 --> 00:17:55,759
end up like your sister,

448
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:56,799
I'll never

449
00:17:56,799 --> 00:17:57,839
forgive myself for the rest of my life.

450
00:17:59,039 --> 00:18:00,000
Then tell me,

451
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:01,880
how do you want me to help you?

452
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:03,960
The thing inside the cuckoo clock,

453
00:18:04,839 --> 00:18:05,559
what exactly is it?

454
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:07,799
It's a flash drive.

455
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:09,279
You must have made a backup,

456
00:18:09,759 --> 00:18:10,240
right?

457
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:11,519
Give it to me.

458
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:13,160
I don't have a backup.

459
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:42,240
Buddy.

460
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:43,240
What time is it?

461
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:44,400
My phone died.

462
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:48,319
It's 10:30.

463
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:49,200
10:30.

464
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:52,000
You're still delivering goods this late?

465
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:53,319
Go back to Chen City.

466
00:18:53,519 --> 00:18:54,680
The client there needs it urgently.

467
00:18:56,440 --> 00:18:58,000
Driving at night isn't easy.

468
00:18:59,839 --> 00:19:00,400
For me?

469
00:19:00,519 --> 00:19:01,559
Thank you, thank you.

470
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:03,039
Take care.

471
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:39,079
It's a bit hot.

472
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:40,720
Thanks.

473
00:19:41,897 --> 00:19:43,538
(Unknown Number)

474
00:19:49,319 --> 00:19:49,880
Hello?

475
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:51,759
Zinuo, it's me.

476
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:53,400
Lei?

477
00:19:53,839 --> 00:19:54,960
This is my other number.

478
00:19:55,279 --> 00:19:56,440
That phone from before,

479
00:19:56,880 --> 00:19:58,079
Li Jin tampered with it.

480
00:19:58,279 --> 00:19:59,599
Since you know she doesn't trust you,

481
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,000
why are you still helping her?

482
00:20:01,319 --> 00:20:02,640
I'm not helping her.

483
00:20:03,319 --> 00:20:04,519
I'm protecting you.

484
00:20:05,119 --> 00:20:06,319
What's inside the cuckoo clock

485
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:08,400
can destroy all of us.

486
00:20:08,799 --> 00:20:10,400
It will only bring you trouble.

487
00:20:10,799 --> 00:20:12,440
You absolutely must stay out of this.

488
00:20:12,599 --> 00:20:13,559
You do have a backup,

489
00:20:14,160 --> 00:20:14,680
don't you?

490
00:20:15,119 --> 00:20:15,920
I do have a backup.

491
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:17,759
But I can't give it to you right now.

492
00:20:18,359 --> 00:20:19,640
I called to tell you

493
00:20:19,839 --> 00:20:20,720
that you must

494
00:20:20,799 --> 00:20:22,160
keep your distance
from this whole thing.

495
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:22,960
Remember that.

496
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,640
Everyone says it's to protect me.

497
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:41,720
For my own good.

498
00:20:42,519 --> 00:20:43,240
And what did they do?

499
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:46,880
She lied to me.

500
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:49,000
I accept that.

501
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:51,559
But I won't let her hurt anyone else.

502
00:20:57,653 --> 00:20:59,848
(Nuo)

503
00:21:02,559 --> 00:21:03,480
Return the money to Yu Ming.

504
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:05,319
That money isn't his.

505
00:21:05,839 --> 00:21:06,799
And it isn't yours either.

506
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,440
That money was left for me
by Chen Liyang.

507
00:21:12,359 --> 00:21:13,200
Consider this me begging you.

508
00:21:15,359 --> 00:21:16,720
I'm begging you, give the money back.

509
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:19,000
This money is to save lives.

510
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:21,880
I'm your mother.

511
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:24,000
We are family.

512
00:21:25,119 --> 00:21:26,119
Why are you always better to outsiders

513
00:21:26,119 --> 00:21:27,119
than you are to me?

514
00:21:27,799 --> 00:21:28,759
Give him the money first.

515
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:30,720
We can talk about the rest later.

516
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:31,960
Nuo,

517
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:33,519
I spent

518
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,359
five years of my life

519
00:21:35,359 --> 00:21:36,200
getting this money.

520
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:37,400
This money was paid for

521
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,359
by Chen Liyang with her life.

522
00:21:38,839 --> 00:21:39,920
You have no right to touch it.

523
00:21:40,279 --> 00:21:41,359
If you have a shred of humanity left,

524
00:21:42,039 --> 00:21:42,960
give the money back.

525
00:21:44,079 --> 00:21:44,720
My child,

526
00:21:45,640 --> 00:21:47,119
can you even tell what's good

527
00:21:47,119 --> 00:21:48,079
and what's evil?

528
00:21:50,519 --> 00:21:51,880
Yu Ming's family was kidnapped

529
00:21:52,599 --> 00:21:53,960
because of his own greed.

530
00:21:54,839 --> 00:21:56,119
I paid the price

531
00:21:56,200 --> 00:21:57,039
for my own greed.

532
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:59,240
Shouldn't he?

533
00:21:59,680 --> 00:22:01,079
That's still not for you to judge.

534
00:22:01,880 --> 00:22:03,200
If you don't return the money,

535
00:22:04,519 --> 00:22:05,119
then I'll take

536
00:22:05,119 --> 00:22:06,200
what's inside the cuckoo clock

537
00:22:06,599 --> 00:22:07,359
and hand it to the police.

538
00:22:09,759 --> 00:22:10,720
Do things really have to be

539
00:22:10,759 --> 00:22:11,960
this absolute?

540
00:22:14,519 --> 00:22:15,599
Let's both calm down.

541
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:18,200
Let's meet face to face.

542
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:39,640
Her fever still isn't going down.

543
00:22:42,039 --> 00:22:43,119
The medicine isn't working.

544
00:22:44,039 --> 00:22:44,640
This won't do.

545
00:22:45,319 --> 00:22:46,119
We have to go to the hospital.

546
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:47,119
Are you insane?

547
00:22:47,599 --> 00:22:48,359
That's suicidal.

548
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:49,400
Go to the hospital?

549
00:22:49,559 --> 00:22:50,559
Might as well just turn ourselves in.

550
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:52,680
What the hell do you know?

551
00:22:56,279 --> 00:22:57,480
She's weak to begin with,

552
00:22:57,519 --> 00:22:58,400
and her heart is bad.

553
00:22:59,319 --> 00:23:00,640
If you let her die on us,

554
00:23:01,759 --> 00:23:03,079
who are we gonna ask for the money?

555
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:12,920
Try giving her more medicine.

556
00:23:13,240 --> 00:23:14,319
We really have to hurry this up.

557
00:23:14,359 --> 00:23:15,359
Don't let her drag on until she's dead.

558
00:23:38,799 --> 00:23:39,440
Ma'am, we're from

559
00:23:39,759 --> 00:23:41,279
the Municipal Criminal
Investigation Unit.

560
00:23:41,559 --> 00:23:42,680
Have you seen this person before?

561
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:43,759
Yeah, I've seen her.

562
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:45,319
She lives right across the corridor.

563
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:46,200
There's a man

564
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:47,359
living here with her.

565
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:48,880
Always wears a hat when he goes out.

566
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:50,440
That man's got a bad temper.

567
00:23:50,559 --> 00:23:51,480
Once I even overheard them

568
00:23:51,480 --> 00:23:52,319
arguing about

569
00:23:52,799 --> 00:23:53,599
getting money.

570
00:23:53,799 --> 00:23:54,799
Did you hear them say

571
00:23:54,839 --> 00:23:55,799
what kind of money?

572
00:23:55,839 --> 00:23:56,880
Couldn't make that out clearly.

573
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:58,359
The soundproofing here in our building

574
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:59,079
